    "name": "Question 20 @ 2022/2023",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The equivalent charge of three capacitors 3µF, 12µF and 4µF that are connected in series across a potential difference of 12V is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "19µC",
        "1.5µC",
        "0.1µC",
        "12µC"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "18µC"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<div style='font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6;'><h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>Series Capacitor Charge Calculation</h3><p>For capacitors in series:</p><p style='background: #f8f9fa; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3498db;'><strong>1/C<sub>eq</sub> = 1/C<sub>1</sub> + 1/C<sub>2</sub> + 1/C<sub>3</sub></strong></p><h4 style='color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 15px;'>Step-by-Step:</h4><ol><li>Calculate equivalent capacitance:<br>1/C<sub>eq</sub> = 1/3 + 1/12 + 1/4 = (4 + 1 + 3)/12 = 8/12 ⇒ C<sub>eq</sub> = 1.5µF</li><li>Charge on capacitors in series:<br>Q = C<sub>eq</sub>V = (1.5µF)(12V) = <strong>18µC</strong></li></ol><p style='color: #e74c3c;'><em>Note: The correct answer (18µC) is not listed among the options, suggesting an error in the question.</em></p></div>"
    },
